                            <comment id="492696" author="ssmirnov" created="Wed, 8 Apr 2026 17:57:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bring up LNet, have at least one local NI configured&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Verify that the local NI status is &quot;up&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use &quot;ip link set&quot; to bring the link associated with the NI to &quot;down&quot;. (This should work with both tcp and o2ib lnets).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use &quot; lnetctl net show&quot; to verify that the local NI status is now &quot;down&quot;, (&quot;fatal&quot; flag should be set, visible with -v4 option)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use &quot;ip link set&quot; to bring the same link back &quot;up&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use &quot; lnetctl net show&quot; to check the NI status.&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
